                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="154083" author="pjones" created="Tue, 31 May 2016 13:55:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that this work has been superceded by the developmentin &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7990&quot; title=&quot; Large bulk IO support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7990&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7990&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="127979" author="panda" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2015 17:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, since so many people requested to make the step automatic, I updated the patch according to Jinshan Xiong&apos;s proposal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="127569" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 16 Sep 2015 21:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have to ask what is the advantage of making read ahead step size configurable? Wouldn&apos;t be simpler to just adjust the read ahead  step to be based on max_pages_per_rpc instead. Also if their is a benefit to making the read ahead step configurable why in megabytes. I think it would be better in pages. Especially since user can pass in strange values that end up having to be rounded to the nearest page anyways.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="127057" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 09:22:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andrew Perepechko (andrew.perepechko@seagate.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/16374&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/16374&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
